==English==

===Etymology===
(1375-1425) From late Middle English ''[[slutte]]'', from ''[[slut#Middle English|slut]]'', "mud". Confer Norwegian ''[[slutr]]'', "sleep", "impure liquid".

===Noun===
{{en-noun|slut|sluts}}
#{{countable}} (''derogatory'') A [[sexual]]ly [[promiscuous]] [[woman]].
#:See also [[WikiSaurus:promiscuous woman]]
#{{countable}} A [[prostitute]].
#{{countable}} {{archaic}} A [[female]] [[dog]].

====Derived terms====
*[[slutty]]

